<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="506" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1507,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">
Only when 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens, R." box="[280,448,1507,1532]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" pagination="139 - 142" refId="ref12650" refString="Mertens, R. (1937) Bemerkungen uber die Rassen von Pelomedusa subrufa (La Cepede). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 117, 139 - 142." type="journal article" year="1937">Mertens (1937</bibRefCitation>
: p. 139) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge, A." box="[590,780,1507,1532]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" pagination="467 - 524" refId="ref12616" refString="Loveridge, A. (1941) Revision of the African terrapin [sic] of the family Pelomedusidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 88, 467 - 524." type="journal article" year="1941">Loveridge (1941</bibRefCitation>
: p. 470) reinstated the scientific name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lacepede, 1788)" baseAuthorityName="Lacepede" baseAuthorityYear="1788" class="Reptilia" family="Pelomedusidae" genus="Pelomedusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[1207,1435,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Pelomedusa subrufa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[158,340,1543,1568]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède, 1788</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
for helmeted terrapins, this name combination found wide acceptance. Previously, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schoepff, 1792)" baseAuthorityName="Schoepff" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Reptilia" family="Pelomedusidae" genus="Pelomedusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="galeata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Pelomedusa galeata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schoepff, I. D." box="[248,421,1579,1604]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref13074" refString="Schoepff, I. D. (1792) Historia Testudinum iconibus illustrata. Ioannes Iacobus Palm, Erlangen, XII + 136 pp., 31 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5109" type="book" year="1792">Schoepff, 1792</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was used by most authors (see below under 
<taxonomicName authority="Schoepff, 1792" authorityName="Schoepff" authorityYear="1792" box="[924,1280,1579,1604]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="galeata">
<emphasis box="[924,1100,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Testudo galeata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schoepff, I. D." box="[1106,1280,1579,1604]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref13074" refString="Schoepff, I. D. (1792) Historia Testudinum iconibus illustrata. Ioannes Iacobus Palm, Erlangen, XII + 136 pp., 31 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5109" type="book" year="1792">Schoepff, 1792</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), even though John Edward Gray in his influential works consistently applied the species name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lacepede" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[1083,1169,1615,1640]" class="Reptilia" family="Pelomedusidae" genus="Pelomedusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[1083,1169,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authority=", Gray 1831: p. 39" authorityName="Gray" authorityPageNumber="39" authorityYear="1831" class="Reptilia" family="Chelidae" genus="Hydraspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[1219,1428,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Hydraspis subrufa</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[151,274,1651,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12093" refString="Gray, J. E. (1831) Synopsis Reptilium; or Short Descriptions of the Species of Reptiles. Part I. - Cataphracta. Tortoises, Crocodiles, and Enaliosaurians. Treuttel, Wurtz, and Co., London, viii + 85 pp." type="book" year="1831">Gray 1831</bibRefCitation>
: p. 39
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lacepede" baseAuthorityYear="1788" box="[378,607,1651,1676]" class="Reptilia" family="Pelomedusidae" genus="Pelomedusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[378,607,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Pelomedusa subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[676,799,1651,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12142" refString="Gray, J. E. (1856 [&quot; 1855 &quot;]) Catalogue of Shield Reptiles in the Collection of the British Museum. Part I. Testudinata (Tortoises). British Museum, London, (1) + 79 + (2) pp., 42 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5491" type="book" year="1856">Gray 1856</bibRefCitation>
: p. 53; 1863: pp. 99–100).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1507,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[335,523,1687,1712]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[335,523,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally coined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[858,1056,1687,1712]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède (1788)</bibRefCitation>
in his “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Histoire Naturelle des Quadrupèdes Ovipares</emphasis>
”, where a specimen from the Royal Cabinet Paris was described under the name “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">La Roussâtre</emphasis>
” (p. 173). In the “ 
<emphasis box="[477,1012,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Synopsis methodica Quadrupedum oviparorum</emphasis>
” of the same work, a folded table in which binominals were applied to the individual species, Lacepède named this terrapin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[1126,1304,1795,1820]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[1126,1304,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[183,371,1831,1856]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède (1788</bibRefCitation>
: p. 173) the terrapin on which he based his description was obtained from Pierre Sonnerat (1745–1814) and came allegedly from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[598,654,1867,1892]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Inde</collectingCountry>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1507,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">
This specimen, which has to be identified with the 
<typeStatus box="[769,867,1903,1928]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepede, 1788" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1788" box="[904,1270,1903,1928]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[904,1083,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[1089,1270,1903,1928]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède, 1788</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is still present in the collection of the Muséum National d’Histoire naturelle (
<bibRefCitation author="Bour, R." box="[881,1006,1939,1964]" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" pagination="531 - 539" refId="ref11305" refString="Bour, R. (1982) Pelomedusa subrufa (Lacepede, 1788), Pelusios subniger (Lacepede, 1788) (Reptilia, Chelonii) et le sejour de Philibert Commerson a Madagascar. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire naturelle, 4 e Serie, Section A, 4, 531 - 539." type="journal article" year="1982">Bour 1982</bibRefCitation>
) and was examined by us; tissue for genetic examination was extracted. The type (MNHN 7970) is a shell of an adult terrapin (straight carapacial length 
<quantity box="[151,257,2011,2036]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.367" pageId="5" pageNumber="506" unit="cm" value="13.67">13.67 cm</quantity>
) with most epidermal scutes missing. Its plastron is broken (
<figureCitation box="[936,1005,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,954,976]" captionTargetBox="[212,1387,200,929]" captionTargetId="figure-447@6.[179,1408,185,941]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal and ventral view of the holotype of Testudo subrufa Bonnaterre, 1789 (MNHN 7970, straight carapacial length 13.67 cm). Scale bar, 3 cm. Photos: M.D. Hofmeyr." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915068" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915068/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="506">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
