<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1045,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
Since the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[948,1083,1045,1070]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="55" refId="ref12417" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2005) Opinion 2104. Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature, 62, 55." type="journal article" year="2005">ICZN 2005</bibRefCitation>
: Opinion 2104, Case 3226) has ruled that 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[273,485,1081,1106]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède’s (1788)</bibRefCitation>
“ 
<emphasis box="[508,1039,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Histoire Naturelle des Quadrupèdes Ovipares</emphasis>
” is an unavailable non-binominal work, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnaterre" box="[226,436,1117,1142]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref11147" refString="Bonnaterre, [P. J.] (1789) Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regnes de la nature. Erpetologie. Panckoucke, Hotel de Thou, Paris, xxviii + 70 + (1) pp., 35 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59326" type="book" year="1789">Bonnaterre (1789)</bibRefCitation>
became author of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[661,844,1117,1142]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[661,844,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and of other names) by re-publishing Lacepède’s descriptions using consistently binominal scientific names. The 
<typeStatus box="[878,926,1154,1178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">type</typeStatus>
status of the terrapin described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède (1788)</bibRefCitation>
and re-described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnaterre" box="[460,661,1189,1214]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref11147" refString="Bonnaterre, [P. J.] (1789) Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regnes de la nature. Erpetologie. Panckoucke, Hotel de Thou, Paris, xxviii + 70 + (1) pp., 35 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59326" type="book" year="1789">Bonnaterre (1789</bibRefCitation>
: p. 28) remains unaffected by this transfer of formal authorship.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1045,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
It is obvious that the original type locality (“ 
<collectingCountry box="[725,780,1225,1250]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Inde</collectingCountry>
”) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[844,1027,1225,1250]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[844,1027,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in error. In accordance with the information provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede" box="[434,626,1261,1286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref12474" refString="Lacepede, [B. G.] de (1788) Histoire naturelle des quadrupedes ovipares et des serpens. Tome premier. Hotel de Thou, Paris, (17) + (1, errata) + 651 pp., 1 folded table, 41 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5036" type="book" year="1788">Lacepède (1788)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens, R." box="[639,808,1261,1286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="139 - 142" refId="ref12650" refString="Mertens, R. (1937) Bemerkungen uber die Rassen von Pelomedusa subrufa (La Cepede). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 117, 139 - 142." type="journal article" year="1937">Mertens (1937</bibRefCitation>
: p. 139) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge, A." box="[957,1148,1261,1286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="467 - 524" refId="ref12616" refString="Loveridge, A. (1941) Revision of the African terrapin [sic] of the family Pelomedusidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 88, 467 - 524." type="journal article" year="1941">Loveridge (1941</bibRefCitation>
: p. 470) believed that the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[353,533,1297,1322]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[353,533,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originates from Sonnerat, who is known to have collected at the Cape of Good Hope. Therefore, they identified the type locality with the Cape. However, based on an extensive discussion of historical details, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bour, R." box="[350,489,1369,1394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="531 - 539" refId="ref11305" refString="Bour, R. (1982) Pelomedusa subrufa (Lacepede, 1788), Pelusios subniger (Lacepede, 1788) (Reptilia, Chelonii) et le sejour de Philibert Commerson a Madagascar. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire naturelle, 4 e Serie, Section A, 4, 531 - 539." type="journal article" year="1982">Bour (1982)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that the 
<typeStatus box="[711,809,1369,1394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[848,1027,1369,1394]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[848,1027,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was most probably not collected by Sonnerat, but by Philibert Commerson (1727–1773), who stayed on 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1100,1405,1430]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
in 1770. Some drawings of Commerson’s Malagasy specimens are still present in the Central Library of the Paris Museum. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bour, R." box="[1294,1436,1441,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="531 - 539" refId="ref11305" refString="Bour, R. (1982) Pelomedusa subrufa (Lacepede, 1788), Pelusios subniger (Lacepede, 1788) (Reptilia, Chelonii) et le sejour de Philibert Commerson a Madagascar. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire naturelle, 4 e Serie, Section A, 4, 531 - 539." type="journal article" year="1982">Bour (1982)</bibRefCitation>
identified one of these drawings with the 
<typeStatus box="[671,769,1477,1502]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">holotype</typeStatus>
and designated “Taolañaro (Fort-Dauphin), République Malagasy [
<collectingCountry box="[275,418,1513,1538]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
]” (p. 535) as type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[757,937,1513,1538]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[757,937,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, probably due to oversight, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bour, R." pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="54 - 80" refId="ref11361" refString="Bour, R. (1985) Les tortues terrestres et d'eau douce de Madagascar et des iles voisines. Madagascar Recherches Scientifique, 18, 54 - 80." type="journal article" year="1985">Bour (1985</bibRefCitation>
: p. 56) endorsed later the Cape of Good Hope as type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[948,1126,1549,1574]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[948,1126,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
again.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1045,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
All of our efforts to generate mtDNA sequences from the 
<typeStatus box="[904,1002,1585,1610]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">holotype</typeStatus>
resulted only in contaminant fungal sequences. Therefore, in the absence of other evidence, we accept the type locality Taolañaro (
<collectingCountry box="[1250,1391,1621,1646]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
), as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bour, R." box="[310,455,1657,1682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="531 - 539" refId="ref11305" refString="Bour, R. (1982) Pelomedusa subrufa (Lacepede, 1788), Pelusios subniger (Lacepede, 1788) (Reptilia, Chelonii) et le sejour de Philibert Commerson a Madagascar. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire naturelle, 4 e Serie, Section A, 4, 531 - 539." type="journal article" year="1982">Bour (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently, the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonnaterre, 1789" authorityName="Bonnaterre" authorityYear="1789" box="[755,1145,1657,1682]" class="Reptilia" family="Testudinidae" genus="Testudo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[755,937,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Testudo subrufa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnaterre" box="[947,1145,1657,1682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref11147" refString="Bonnaterre, [P. J.] (1789) Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regnes de la nature. Erpetologie. Panckoucke, Hotel de Thou, Paris, xxviii + 70 + (1) pp., 35 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59326" type="book" year="1789">Bonnaterre, 1789</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
refers to lineage VIII of 
<bibRefCitation author="Vargas-Ramirez, M. &amp; Vences, M. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Daniels, S. R. &amp; Glaw, F. &amp; Hofmeyr, M. D. &amp; Kuchling, G. &amp; Maran, J. &amp; Papenfuss, T. J. &amp; Siroky, P. &amp; Vieites, D. R. &amp; Fritz, U." box="[151,480,1693,1718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="428 - 440" refId="ref13781" refString="Vargas-Ramirez, M., Vences, M., Branch, W. R., Daniels, S. R., Glaw, F., Hofmeyr, M. D., Kuchling, G., Maran, J., Papenfuss, T. J., Siroky, P., Vieites, D. R. &amp; Fritz, U. (2010) Deep genealogical lineages in the widely distributed African helmeted terrapin: evidence from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA (Testudines: Pelomedusidae: Pelomedusa subrufa). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 56, 428 - 440. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2010.03.019" type="journal article" year="2010">
Vargas-Ramírez 
<emphasis box="[338,396,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
, which is known to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[807,944,1693,1718]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1069,1694,1717]" name="Botswana" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Botswana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">the Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[242,327,1729,1754]" name="Malawi" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Malawi</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[388,485,1729,1754]" name="Namibia" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Namibia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[503,571,1729,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1100,1122]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,201,1075]" captionTargetId="figure-427@5.[151,1436,195,1080]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum Likelihood tree for Pelomedusa, based on 1848 bp of mitochondrial DNA (12S, cyt b, ND4+tRNAs), rooted with Pelusios sinuatus. The tree topology completely matches the one inferred by Bayesian analyses. Numbers along nodes indicate bootstrap support and Bayesian posterior probabilities greater than 50 or 0.95, respectively (not shown for some terminal clades with short branches). Sample codes are voucher numbers; see Table S1 for explanation. Name-bearing types (red) and paralectotypes or topotypic samples (blue) highlighted. On the right, mitochondrial lineages of Vargas-Ramírez et al. (2010) indicated. No topotypic material of Pelomedusa galeata orangensis Hewitt, 1935 could be sequenced. However, the lost holotype is thought to come from the vicinity of Kimberley (South Africa) and all South African samples belong to lineage IX, so it can be concluded that Pelomedusa galeata orangensis represents the same lineage. Inset: Helmeted terrapin from the Addo Elephant National Park, South Africa. Photo: M. Gregorič." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915066/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The Malagasy populations are thought to be introduced from continental Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Vargas-Ramirez, M. &amp; Vences, M. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Daniels, S. R. &amp; Glaw, F. &amp; Hofmeyr, M. D. &amp; Kuchling, G. &amp; Maran, J. &amp; Papenfuss, T. J. &amp; Siroky, P. &amp; Vieites, D. R. &amp; Fritz, U." box="[237,551,1765,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="428 - 440" refId="ref13781" refString="Vargas-Ramirez, M., Vences, M., Branch, W. R., Daniels, S. R., Glaw, F., Hofmeyr, M. D., Kuchling, G., Maran, J., Papenfuss, T. J., Siroky, P., Vieites, D. R. &amp; Fritz, U. (2010) Deep genealogical lineages in the widely distributed African helmeted terrapin: evidence from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA (Testudines: Pelomedusidae: Pelomedusa subrufa). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 56, 428 - 440. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2010.03.019" type="journal article" year="2010">
Vargas-Ramírez 
<emphasis box="[427,484,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wong, R. A. &amp; Fong, J. J. &amp; Papenfuss, T. J." box="[563,762,1765,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" pagination="575 - 585" refId="ref13970" refString="Wong, R. A., Fong, J. J. &amp; Papenfuss, T. J. (2010) Phylogeography of the African helmeted terrapin, Pelomedusa subrufa: genetic structure, dispersal, and human introduction. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 61, 575 - 585." type="journal article" year="2010">
Wong 
<emphasis box="[636,694,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). If lineage VIII is deemed to be taxonomically distinct, the name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bonnaterre, 1789)" baseAuthorityName="Bonnaterre" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[218,668,1801,1826]" class="Reptilia" family="Pelomedusidae" genus="Pelomedusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Testudines" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subrufa">
<emphasis box="[218,448,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Pelomedusa subrufa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnaterre" box="[462,660,1801,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" refId="ref11147" refString="Bonnaterre, [P. J.] (1789) Tableau encyclopedique et methodique des trois regnes de la nature. Erpetologie. Panckoucke, Hotel de Thou, Paris, xxviii + 70 + (1) pp., 35 plates. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59326" type="book" year="1789">Bonnaterre, 1789</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
will have to be restricted to this taxon.
</paragraph>
